ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Equine herpesvirus is also known as rhinopneumonitis and is a viral
disease (EHV-1) caused by a herpesvirus. It may present as a severe
respiratory infection, but it may also cause a neurological disease
or abortion in pregnant mares. There is a vaccine for it. The
immunity conferred from the disease or the vaccine is relatively
short in duration. Horses on the show or racing circuit are often
vaccinated every 6 months. - Mod.TG]

[The original posting erroneously identified the State of this outbreak as
Kentucky when it is in New Jersey. The title has been changed to reflect
the true geographic location. - Mod.MPP]
